<p>In this example, we want System B to execute something after System A窶冱 Stage 1. We define <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">SystemB::Stage2</code> to execute such code since we know that Stage 2 always executes after Stage 1. If we define stage functions for both systems for the same stage, the execution order is non-deterministic.</p>

